<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="much-adv">much <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /mʌtʃ/    美 /mʌtʃ/  </p>
<p>(more, most)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>经常；频繁：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He doesn’t swim much. 
他不常游泳。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>很；非常：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>much to our surprise 
令我们非常吃惊的是</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Thank you <strong>very much</strong> for your coming. 
非常感谢您的光临。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m much pleased with it.
我对此非常满意。</p></div>

<h3 id="much-too-too-much">辨析 much too, too much</h3>
<p><strong>much too ** 意为“太”、“非常”，后接形容词或副词。
</strong>too much ** 意为“太多”，可用作形容词词组，后接不可数名词；也可用作名词词组或副词词组。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A neighbor complained the kids were making too much noise. 
有位邻居抱怨孩子们太吵了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have eaten too much (food) today. 
我今天吃得太多了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You worry too much. 
你过于担心了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>...多；更：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The crop was growing much slower than he expected. 
庄稼比他预期的长得慢多了。</p><footer>2008 广东</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This is much the best way to do it. 
这是做这件事最好的方法。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="as-much">as much</h3>
<p>1.<strong>同样数量；同样的事：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tony lent me the money, hoping that I’d do as much for him.
托尼借给我钱，希望我以后也会为他做同样的事。</p><footer>2012 全国</footer></div>

<h3 id="as-much-as">as much as</h3>
<p>1.<strong>像…那么多；多达：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She spends as much as $2,000 on clothes every month. 
她每月买衣服的开销高达2000美元。</p></div>

<h3 id="as-much-as_1">as much … as</h3>
<p>1.<strong>和…同样多的；和…一样：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We didn’t spend as much time at the museum as I had hoped.
我们在博物馆花的时间没有我期望的那么长。</p></div>

<h3 id="as-much-as-sb-can-could-do">as much as sb can / could (do)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>尽某人最大努力 (as much as possible)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have done as much as I could do to help him. 
我已尽力去帮助他了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Students are encouraged to read as much as possible outside school. 
我们鼓励学生在课外尽量多阅读。</p></div>

<h3 id="how-much">how much</h3>
<p>1.<strong>多少；什么价钱：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Any owner will tell you how much joy a pet brings.
任何一位宠物的主人都会告诉你宠物会带来多少欢乐。</p><footer> 2010 全国</footer></div>

<h3 id="not-nothing-much">not / nothing much</h3>
<p>1.<strong>没什么：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Is there anything wrong, Bob? You look sad.
鲍勃，怎么了？你看起来很难过。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Oh, nothing much. In fact, I was just thinking of my friends back home.
哦，没什么。事实上我刚才在想念家乡的朋友们。</p></div>

<h3 id="so-much-for">so much for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[用于结束某个话题] 到此为止：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>So much for all those introductions. It’s time to get down to business. 
就介绍这么多吧，该开始工作了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The data is about the moon's composition, such as how<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ ice and other treasures it contains.  （2020全国改）  </li>
<li>I wanted to be a teacher because I liked my English teacher too much.  （2019全国  改错）  </li>
<li>— What did you do last weekend?
— Oh, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (没什么).  （2014 全国改）  </li>
<li>It’s high time you had your hair cut; it’s getting <strong><em>_</em></strong>_. 
  （2009 全国）<br />
A.too much long<br />
B.much too long<br />
C.long too much<br />
D.too long much  </li>
<li>Usually John would be late for meetings. But this time, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (令我非常吃惊的是), he arrived on time.  （2009 北京改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. much  2. too → very / so  3. nothing / not much  4. B  5. much to my surprise  </p></div>